1. Installing Yosys

Yosys is an open-source synthesis tool for Verilog designs.

Steps:
# Update package list
sudo apt-get update

# Clone Yosys repository
git clone https://github.com/YosysHQ/yosys.git

# Navigate to the Yosys folder
cd yosys

# Install make (if not installed)
sudo apt install make

# Install dependencies
sudo apt-get install build-essential clang bison flex \
libreadline-dev gawk tcl-dev libffi-dev git \
graphviz xdot pkg-config python3 libboost-system-dev \
libboost-python-dev libboost-filesystem-dev zlib1g-dev

# Configure for GCC
make config-gcc

# Build Yosys
make

# Install Yosys
sudo make install

2. Installing Icarus Verilog (iverilog)

Icarus Verilog is a Verilog simulation and compilation tool.

Steps:
# Update package list
sudo apt-get update

# Install Icarus Verilog
sudo apt-get install iverilog

3. Installing GTKWave

GTKWave is a waveform viewer for simulation output.

Steps:
# Update package list
sudo apt-get update

# Install GTKWave
sudo apt install gtkwave
 After completing these steps, Yosys, Icarus Verilog and GTKWave will be installed and ready for use.
